{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"All direct and transitive dependencies are extracted from the manifest and included in the vulnerability check.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure boundary is module handoff: manifest parser/resolver output must be passed into vulnerability-check input. A unit test of only parsing or only traversal can miss dropped transitive deps during wiring. Rejected System because behavior text does not require real network/OS/subprocess; an in-process fake vulnerability client can expose missing dependency IDs. Rejected Agentic/Workflow because no AI/ML decision is involved.","test_description":"Run scanner components together with a fixture manifest containing direct and nested transitive deps; use a fake vulnerability client that records queried package@version inputs; assert every expected direct/transitive dependency is queried exactly once.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.3,"Integration":0.65,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"The vulnerability database query returns results that match the exact version ranges in the manifest, not just the package name.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Real failure can sit at external API contract boundary: range syntax/semver interpretation may differ from local assumptions, and an in-process fake can falsely pass. MOCK-HIDE applies because a stub that 'understands' local expectations may not reproduce real API filtering quirks. Rejected Agentic/Workflow because behavior is deterministic API semantics, not model judgment.","test_description":"Against a real test/sandbox vulnerability API, submit manifests with same package name but different constrained ranges and assert returned CVEs differ according to those ranges (including a case where name matches but version range should exclude a CVE).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.28,"System":0.7,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The severity sorting places Critical above High above Medium above Low, with CVEs of the same severity sorted by CVSS score.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"This is pure ordering logic within one comparator/sort function; no required module boundary, I/O, or external dependency. Rejected Integration because behavior text is algorithmic and does not describe cross-module handoff failure.","test_description":"Call the sort function with unsorted CVE fixtures spanning all severities and tie cases; assert final order is severity rank first, then descending CVSS within equal severity.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.9,"Integration":0.1,"System":0.0,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"The manifest modification changes only the affected dependency's version, leaving all other entries unchanged.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure appears when parser/editor/serializer are wired: updating one dependency can accidentally rewrite unrelated entries. A single-function unit test can miss preservation behavior across read-modify-write modules. Rejected System because real OS/filesystem is not required; compare before/after content in-process.","test_description":"Run manifest update pipeline on fixture manifests (package.json/requirements variant), bump one target dependency, and assert semantic equality of all non-target entries plus unchanged lock/order fields expected to be preserved by the updater.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.25,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The auto-generated pull request is created on the real repository with the correct single-dependency diff.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Behavior explicitly requires real repository